<article>
<p>
The mathematical process of mixing letters and numbers together to form equation(s) is known as <strong>algebra</strong>. It also involves using letters to represent numbers in algebraic sentence. 
<br>
<strong>Algebraic sentence</strong> is a statement with equals sign e.g. y + 3 = 11

<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h2 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Rules for Solving Algebraic Equation/Sentence</h2>
</div>

i.	Look for like terms, put them together on the same of the equation and simplify accordingly.
<br>
ii.	If any number or letter crosses the equals sign (=), its sign will change e.g. from positive sign (+) to negative sign (-) vice versa. 
<br>
iii.	Watch out for coefficient of letter(s) to easily evaluate the equation appropriately e.g. 2x has coefficient of 2.
<br>
<strong>Note: coefficient</strong> is the number in front of letter(s) or alphabet(s) in algebraic sentence.
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Algebraic Equations with Addition Sign (+)</h3>
</div>
<strong>Example 1 </strong>
<br>
Evaluate (i) a = 5 + 6 (ii)9 + 7 = c (iii)8 + f = 2 and (iV)u + u + u = 30.
<br>
<strong>Solution</strong>
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col border-right border-danger">
    (i.)	
    <br>
    a = 5 + 6
    <br>
    a = <strong>11</strong>
    <br>    
    (ii.)	
    <br>
    9 + 7 = c
    <br>
    c = <strong>16</strong>
    <br>
    (iii.)
    <br>	
    8 + f = 2
    <br>
    f = 2 - 8
    <br>              
    f = <strong>-6 </strong>
    <br>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
    (iv.)	
    <br>
    u + u + u = 30
    <br>
    3u = 30
    <br>
    Divide both sides by 3 since coefficient of u => 3
    <br>
    u = <b>10</b>
    </div>
  </div>
  </div>




<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Algebraic Equations with Minus Sign (-)</h3>
</div>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
Evaluate (i) y = 14 – 4 (ii) 18 – 7 = p and (iii) 7 – m = 6
<br>
<strong>Solution </strong>
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col border-right border-danger">
    (i.)
    <br>	
    y = 14 – 4
    <br>
    y = <strong>10 </strong>
    <br>
    (ii.)	
    <br>
    18 – 7 = p
   p = <strong>11</strong>
    <br>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
    (iii.)
    <br>
    7 – m = 6
    <br>
7 = 6 + m
<br>
m + 6  =  7
<br>
m = <strong>1</strong>
</div>
</div>
</div>


