<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Algebraic Substitution</h3>
</div>
This involves replacing the letter with number in algebraic equation. The examples below show how to easily do that;
<br>
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col border-right border-danger">
    <strong>Example 1 </strong>
    <br>
    Evaluate x + 5, 9 + x, x + 3, 19x when x = 3
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    <b>i.</b>	x + 5 = <b>3</b> + 5 = 8
    <br>
    <b>ii.</b>	9 + x = 9 + <b>3</b> = 12
    <br>
    <b>iii.</b>	19x = 19(<b>3</b>) = 57
    </div>
    <div class="col">
    <strong>Example 2</strong>
    <br>
    A mother is 42 years old and her daughter is k years old. If the difference in their age is 28 years. What is the daughter’s age?
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    42 – k = 28
    <br>
    k + 28 = 42
    <br>
    k = 42 - 28
    <br>
    k = 14
    <br>
    The daughter’s age =><strong> 14 years </strong>
    </div>
  </div>
